"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.10.5\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.10.5</span> Anointing oil</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">יִצְהָר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(yitshar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:14\">ZEC 4:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">שֶׁמֶן, מִשְׁחָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(shemen mishchah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:6\">EXO 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:7\">EXO 29:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:21\">EXO 29:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:25\">EXO 30:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:25\">EXO 30:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:31\">EXO 30:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:11\">EXO 31:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:8\">EXO 35:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:15\">EXO 35:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:28\">EXO 35:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:29\">EXO 37:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:38\">EXO 39:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:9\">EXO 40:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:2\">LEV 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:10\">LEV 8:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:12\">LEV 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:7\">LEV 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:10\">LEV 21:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:12\">LEV 21:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:16\">NUM 4:16</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἔλαιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(elaion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:46\">LUK 7:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:9\">HEB 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir45:15\">SIR 45:15</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Plain olive oil was used to anoint kings and sometimes prophets to dedicate them for their tasks.</p>\n<p>The preparation of a special perfumed oil is commanded in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:23\">EXO 30:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:24\">EXO 30:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:25\">EXO 30:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:26\">EXO 30:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:27\">EXO 30:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:28\">EXO 30:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:29\">EXO 30:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:30\">EXO 30:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:31\">EXO 30:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:32\">EXO 30:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:33\">EXO 30:33</a>. It was for anointing the priests as well as the Tabernacle and furniture in the Tabernacle. It set them aside as “holy.” It had an olive oil base mixed with a variety of aromatic spices.</p>\n<p>See also <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.15.1 Oil, ointment&lt;REALIA:1.15.1&gt;</a> and <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">9.3 Olive oil&lt;REALIA:9.3&gt;</a>.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The anointing of a king was primarily a religious act, not a political one.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
